<p data-start="756" data-end="1059">With a Google Scholar profile, you can gather your publications, research interests, and citation counts in one place, making it easier to connect with academic circles. Creating a profile before starting your studies in Turkey is a great step toward increasing your academic visibility.</p>
<h2 class="JlqpRe"><span class="JCzEY tNxQIb"><span class="CSkcDe">How to Get Your Google Scholar Profile ID?</span></span></h2>
<ol data-start="191" data-end="767">
<li data-start="191" data-end="337">
<p data-start="194" data-end="229"><strong data-start="194" data-end="227"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Log in to Google Scholar.</a></strong></p>
<ul data-start="233" data-end="337">
<li data-start="233" data-end="298">
<p data-start="235" data-end="298">Go to the Google Scholar website.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="302" data-end="337">
<p data-start="304" data-end="337">Sign in with your Google account.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="339" data-end="469">
<p data-start="342" data-end="366"><strong data-start="342" data-end="364">Go to your profile.</strong></p>
<ul data-start="370" data-end="469">
<li data-start="370" data-end="469">
<p data-start="372" data-end="469">Open your profile page by clicking your name or profile picture in the top-right menu.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="471" data-end="767">
<p data-start="474" data-end="512"><strong data-start="474" data-end="510">Copy the profile ID from the URL.</strong></p>
<ul data-start="516" data-end="767">
<li data-start="516" data-end="650">
<p data-start="518" data-end="564">Your profile page address will look like this:</p>
<div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary">
<div class="sticky top-9"> </div>
<div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre!">https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=AbCdEfGhIJkC&amp;hl=<span class="hljs-built_in">tr</span><br />
</code></div>
</div>
</li>
<li data-start="654" data-end="724">
<p data-start="656" data-end="724">The part that says <strong data-start="665" data-end="688">“user=AbCdEfGhIJkC”</strong> is your <strong data-start="701" data-end="721">profile ID</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="728" data-end="767">
<p data-start="730" data-end="767">So, the ID in the example is: <strong data-start="749" data-end="765">AbCdEfGhIJkC</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h4 data-start="774" data-end="797">Where to Use It?</h4>
<ul data-start="798" data-end="997">
<li data-start="798" data-end="832">
<p data-start="800" data-end="832">When linking in your <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-akademik-portfolyo-olusturma/">academic CV</a></p>
</li>
<li data-start="833" data-end="868">
<p data-start="835" data-end="868">In university/institutional applications</p>
</li>
<li data-start="869" data-end="931">
<p data-start="871" data-end="931">On platforms like ORCID, ResearchGate, and personal websites</p>
</li>
<li data-start="932" data-end="997">
<p data-start="934" data-end="997">So others can find you directly on Google Scholar</p>
</li>
</ul>
<div class="p8Jhnd">
<div class="aj35ze"> </div>
</div>
<h2 data-start="1066" data-end="1101">The Importance of a Google Scholar Profile</h2>
<p data-start="1103" data-end="1182">As an international student adapting to the academic environment in Turkey:</p>
<ul data-start="1183" data-end="1410">
<li data-start="1183" data-end="1232">
<p data-start="1185" data-end="1232">You can make your research history visible.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1233" data-end="1315">
<p data-start="1235" data-end="1315">Your professors and potential collaborators can easily find your work.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1316" data-end="1410">
<p data-start="1318" data-end="1410">You present a more professional image for scholarships and research projects you apply for.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="1417" data-end="1462">How to Create a Google Scholar Profile</h2>
<ol data-start="1464" data-end="2168">
<li data-start="1464" data-end="1603">
<p data-start="1467" data-end="1603"><strong data-start="1467" data-end="1502">Log in with your Google account.</strong><br data-start="1502" data-end="1505" />Go to the Google Scholar website and sign in with your Gmail account.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1605" data-end="1831">
<p data-start="1608" data-end="1641"><strong data-start="1608" data-end="1639">Enter your profile information.</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1645" data-end="1831">
<li data-start="1645" data-end="1736">
<p data-start="1647" data-end="1736">Your name, affiliation (the university you will enroll at in Turkey), and academic email address.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1740" data-end="1831">
<p data-start="1742" data-end="1831">Select your research areas (e.g., psychology, engineering, international relations).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1833" data-end="2024">
<p data-start="1836" data-end="1856"><strong data-start="1836" data-end="1854">Add publications.</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1860" data-end="2024">
<li data-start="1860" data-end="1933">
<p data-start="1862" data-end="1933">If you have previous articles, conference papers, or project reports, add them.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1937" data-end="2024">
<p data-start="1939" data-end="2024">You can choose from Google’s suggested list or add publications manually.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="2026" data-end="2168">
<p data-start="2029" data-end="2168"><strong data-start="2029" data-end="2064">Make your profile public.</strong><br data-start="2064" data-end="2067" />This allows both the academic community in Turkey and the global community to access your work.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 data-start="2175" data-end="2212">How to Edit Your Profile</h2>
<p data-start="2214" data-end="2304">As your studies in Turkey progress, you will need to add new work. To do this:</p>
<ul data-start="2305" data-end="2574">
<li data-start="2305" data-end="2385">
<p data-start="2307" data-end="2385">Keep your name, affiliation, and research interests up to date using the <strong data-start="2307" data-end="2325">Edit</strong> option.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2386" data-end="2439">
<p data-start="2388" data-end="2439">Regularly add your new articles or papers.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2440" data-end="2504">
<p data-start="2442" data-end="2504">Keep your profile clean by removing incorrectly added publications.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2505" data-end="2574">
<p data-start="2507" data-end="2574">Add a profile picture for a more professional look.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="2581" data-end="2633">Studying in Turkey and Expanding Your Academic Network</h2>
<p data-start="2635" data-end="2927">Your Google Scholar profile makes it easier to build academic connections with professors, research groups, and other international students you will meet in Turkey. It also provides an advantage when you want to participate in projects supported by programs like Erasmus, Mevlana, or TÜBİTAK.</p>
<p data-start="2946" data-end="3238">For international students planning to study in Turkey, <strong data-start="3011" data-end="3049">creating a Google Scholar profile</strong> is one of the most important steps you can take to strengthen your academic identity. Set up your profile before starting university, update it regularly, and make your work visible.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How do I get a Google Scholar profile ID?</h3>
<p>When you open your profile, the code after the “user=” part in the URL in your browser&#8217;s address bar is your profile ID.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is a Google Scholar ID?</h3>
<p>Your Google Scholar ID is the unique number that identifies your personal profile on the platform.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Where can I access academic articles?</h3>
<p>You can access academic articles through Google Scholar, university libraries, and research databases.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is Google Scholar?</h3>
<p>Google Scholar is a free search engine that indexes articles, theses, books, and academic publications, and provides citation information.</p></p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-05-07T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:51:55Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-google-scholar-and-academic-profiles-in-turkey' );
