ide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-psychological-counseling-at-universities-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-psychological-counseling-at-universities-in-turkey/","name":"A Guide to Psychological Counseling at Universities in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-03T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-03T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"A Guide to Psychological Counseling at Universities in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-03T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-03T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover the psychological counseling services available at universities in Turkey. Learn how to get support and take a step towards a healthier future during your studies!","name":"A Guide to Psychological Counseling at Universities in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-psychological-counseling-at-universities-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-psychological-counseling-at-universities-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-psychological-counseling-at-universities-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, Turkey has made significant advancements in the field of psychological counseling. The psychological counseling programs offered at universities provide students with opportunities for both academic and personal development.</p>
<h2 id="psikolojik-danisman-hangi-universitelerde-var" class="wp-block-heading">Which Universities Offer Psychological Counseling?</h2>
<div id="model-response-message-contentr_5ec4a1d4c0822a97" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" dir="ltr">
<p>In Turkey, <b>almost every university</b> has a <b>Psychological Counseling and Guidance Unit (PDR)</b> or a similar center to support students&#8217; mental health. This is a common practice encouraged by the Council of Higher Education (YÖK) to support the social, personal, and academic development of students.</p>
<h3>Structure of Psychological Support Units at Universities</h3>
<p>Although their names may vary (Psychological Counseling Center, Student Guidance Center, etc.), these units generally offer the following services for <b>free</b>:</p>
<h4>1. Individual Psychological Counseling</h4>
<p>These are one-on-one sessions conducted with <b>strict confidentiality</b> to help students cope with personal, social, emotional, or academic issues.</p>
<h4>2. Group Work and Workshops</h4>
<p>These are group activities where students come together for support on topics such as <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-sinav-kaygisi/"><b>test anxiety</b></a>, <b>stress management</b>, <b>communication skills</b>, <b>time management</b>, and <b>building self-confidence</b>.</p>
<h4>3. Psycho-Education and Seminars</h4>
<p>These are seminars and published guidance materials organized to inform the student community about general mental health topics and to raise awareness.</p>
<h4>Example Universities and Unit Names:</h4>
<p>You can find these units at many universities in different cities across Turkey. Here are some examples:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Boğaziçi Üniversitesi:</b> Student Guidance and <a href="https://burem.bogazici.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Psychological Counseling Center <b>(BÜREM)</b></a></li>
<li><b>Koç Üniversitesi:</b> Guidance Service</li>
<li><b>İstanbul Üniversitesi:</b> Guidance, Counseling, and Social Support Unit</li>
<li><b>Üsküdar Üniversitesi:</b> Psychological Counseling Unit</li>
<li><b>İstanbul Bilgi Üniversitesi:</b> Psychological Counseling Unit</li>
<li><b>Erciyes Üniversitesi:</b> Psychological Counseling and Guidance Application and Research Center <b>(<a href="https://errem.erciyes.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ERREM</a>)</b></li>
<li><b>Akdeniz Üniversitesi:</b> Psychological Counseling and Guidance Service affiliated with the Department of Health, Culture, and Sports</li>
<li><b>Yeditepe Üniversitesi:</b> Psychological Counseling and Guidance Unit</li>
</ul>
<h4>Important Note for International Students</h4>
<p>As an international student, before seeking support, be sure to contact your university&#8217;s PDR unit to confirm whether you can <b>receive services in English</b> or your native language. Universities in large cities with a high number of international students usually have more resources in this regard.</p>
<p><b>The First Step to Take:</b></p>
<p>Searching for the <b>&#8220;Psychological Counseling and Guidance&#8221;</b> heading on your university&#8217;s website, under the <b>&#8220;Student Affairs Department&#8221;</b> or <b>&#8220;Health, Culture, and Sports Department (SKS)&#8221;</b> sections, will help you find the most accurate information.</p>
</div>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also take a look at our article on <a title="Mental Health Services and Psychological Support in Turkey" href="https://https://roadtostudy.com//turkiyede-mental-saglik-hizmetleri/">Mental Health Services and Psychological Support in Turkey</a>.</p>
<h2 id="psikolojik-danisman-olmak-icin-hangi-universite-mezunu-olmak-gerekir" class="wp-block-heading">What University Degree is Required to Become a Psychological Counselor?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To become a psychological counselor, it is generally necessary to have a degree in psychology, guidance and psychological counseling, social work, or from a faculty of education. Graduates from these departments can specialize by pursuing a master&#8217;s degree in psychological counseling. Additionally, some universities may require a specific GPA and language proficiency for admission to their psychological counseling programs.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Key Educational Stages</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Undergraduate Education</strong>: A 4-year bachelor&#8217;s degree in psychology or a related field.</li>
<li><strong>Master&#8217;s Degree</strong>: A 1-2 year master&#8217;s program in psychological counseling or guidance.</li>
<li><strong>Internship and Practical Training</strong>: Completing an internship and gaining practical experience as part of the educational process.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-psikolojik-danismanlik-egitimi-firsatlar-ve-zorluklar" class="wp-block-heading">Psychological Counseling Education in Turkey: Opportunities and Challenges</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Psychological counseling education in Turkey offers students many opportunities, but they may also face some challenges.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Opportunities</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Quality Education</strong>: Many universities in Turkey offer education that meets international standards.</li>
<li><strong>Scholarship Opportunities</strong>: Public and private universities offer scholarship options for international students.</li>
<li><strong>Practical Experience</strong>: The opportunity to do internships during your studies provides students with real-world experience.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Challenges</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Competition</strong>: The growing competition in the field of psychological counseling requires students to continuously improve themselves.</li>
<li><strong>Educational Process</strong>: The long and intensive educational process can be a challenging experience for students.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-psikolojik-danismanlik-alaninda-kariyer-olanaklari" class="wp-block-heading">Career Opportunities in Psychological Counseling in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Career opportunities in the field of psychological counseling are quite broad. Graduates have the chance to work in various sectors. Here are some career options:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>School Counselor</strong>: Provides counseling services to students in schools.</li>
<li><strong>Clinical Psychologist</strong>: Offers solutions to individuals&#8217; psychological problems in healthcare institutions.</li>
<li><strong>Private Practice Counselor</strong>: Can conduct individual or group therapy in their own offices.</li>
<li><strong>Research Assistant</strong>: The opportunity to pursue an academic career at universities.</li>
<li><strong>Social Worker</strong>: Can contribute to society by working in social service organizations.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="psikolojik-danismanlikta-uygulamali-egitim-turkiyedeki-uygulama-alanlari" class="wp-block-heading">Practical Training in Psychological Counseling: Application Areas in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Practical training holds a significant place in the field of psychological counseling. Universities in Turkey offer students various practical training areas. These areas include:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>School Placements</strong>: Students can gain real-life counseling experience by interning in schools.</li>
<li><strong>Clinical Placements</strong>: They can gain clinical experience by interning in hospitals or private clinics.</li>
<li><strong>Social Service Organizations</strong>: They can work in social services to seek solutions to societal problems.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers many opportunities for those who wish to study in the field of psychological counseling. With its quality universities, practical training opportunities, and wide range of career options, Turkey has become an attractive center for young people who want to develop themselves in this field. A psychological counseling education not only provides academic knowledge but also contributes to the personal development of individuals. If you are considering a career in this field, we recommend that you carefully research the universities in Turkey and the programs they offer.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What documents are required for psychological counseling education in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To study psychological counseling, you generally need a high school diploma, a university acceptance letter, health insurance, and visa application documents.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long does psychological counseling education take in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Psychological counseling education takes 4 years at the undergraduate level and 1-2 years at the master&#8217;s level.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What skills are important in the field of psychological counseling?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Communication skills, empathy, problem-solving ability, and a strong ethical understanding are important skills in the field of psychological counseling.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the job prospects in the field of psychological counseling in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Job opportunities in psychological counseling vary depending on the graduate&#8217;s competencies and experience. However, demand in this field is generally high.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the importance of doing an internship during psychological counseling education?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">An internship offers students the opportunity to apply their theoretical knowledge in practice and gain real-world experience, which increases their chances of finding a job after graduation.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-05-03T07:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:51:41Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-psychological-counseling-at-universities-in-turkey';
