ts When Shopping Online?</h2>
<div id="model-response-message-contentr_e4241c58490a5a2a" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" dir="ltr">
<p>To make secure payments when shopping online, start by using a <b>virtual card</b>. Virtual cards are temporary cards you create with a specific spending limit, separate from your main account. Even if your details are stolen, your main balance remains protected.</p>
<p>Other secure methods include:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>3D Secure:</b> Confirm the transaction with an additional password sent to your mobile phone during payment. This prevents unauthorized use even if your card details are stolen.</li>
<li><b>Digital Wallets:</b> Use mobile payment systems (Apple Pay, Google Pay, etc.) that allow you to pay through an encrypted layer without sharing your card details with the merchant.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Tips for a Secure Shopping Environment</h4>
<p>Before making a payment, ensure the site you are shopping on is secure:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Check the Address Bar:</b> Verify that the site&#8217;s address begins with <b><code>https://</code></b> and has a <b>padlock icon</b> next to it. This indicates that your data is encrypted.</li>
<li><b>Trusted Retailers:</b> Prefer well-known e-commerce sites. For unfamiliar sites, be sure to check their <b>ETBİS registration</b> (Turkey&#8217;s Electronic Commerce Information System) and customer reviews.</li>
<li><b>Avoid Public Wi-Fi:</b> Do not use public, unsecured Wi-Fi networks for payment transactions; opt for your secure home network instead.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Personal Security Measures</h4>
<p>Continue to maintain your security even after shopping:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Passwords:</b> Do not use your banking passwords on shopping sites; create strong, unique passwords for each site.</li>
<li><b>Monitor:</b> Check the <b>SMS notification</b> from your bank after the transaction. Regularly review your credit card statements and report any unauthorized transactions to your bank immediately.</li>
<li><b>Log Out:</b> Always <b>log out</b> of your account on the site after completing your transaction.</li>
</ul>
</div>
